    "Jiao et al. (2023) present a more preliminary study using ChatGPT (GPT-3) for MT.",
    "Their analysis is deemed preliminary since it contains only 50 sentences for every set/condition and is additionally limited by the fact that they only employ automatic evaluation metrics.",
    "Both studies, however, find that while GPT models can perform competitively with existing MT systems in highresource 14 settings/languages, they significantly underperform when used in low-resource setting or for distant language paris (Hendy et al., 2023; Jiao et al., 2023).",
    "Jiao et al. (2023) re-evaluated the performance with launch of GPT-4 (March 15, 2023) observing that the performance of ChatGPT based on GPT-4 became more comparable to commercial translation systems for more distant languages. 15 Wang et al.",
    "(2023) compare commercial MT systems (Google Translate 16, DeepL 17, and Tencent TranSmart 18) and document-level NMT models with GPT models and focus particularly on evaluating their discourse awareness through automatic and human evaluations."
